Six deaths were among residents of long-term care facilities, which now account for roughly 18 percent of confirmed coronavirus cases in Maine.
The additional 36 confirmed cases represent a 5 percent increase over Tuesday and a 43 percent increase from one week earlier.
Shah reported that there are now 137 confirmed cases among residents or staff at long-term care facilities in Maine.
